description: Developing nations have criticized the $300 billion annual climate finance commitment from wealthy countries as insufficient at the Cop29 summit in Baku. While a deal was reached, establishing a $1.3 trillion target with significant reliance on private funding, developing nations argued for a greater commitment from historical emitters to address the disproportionate impact of climate change on poorer countries.
title: Cop29 agrees to $300 billion deal, India says amount 'abysmally poor'

description: Amazon is offering its German employees the option to work from home up to two days a week, deviating from its global five-day office mandate. This exception comes amidst employee resistance and contrasts with Amazon's stricter stance compared to other tech giants.
title: Amazon makes exception for this one country in its global RTO policy

description: The BJP's resounding victory in the Maharashtra assembly elections has re-established Prime Minister Modi's political dominance. This win, following close on the heels of their Haryana victory, empowers the BJP to aggressively pursue its core agenda, including the implementation of a Uniform Civil Code and the 'One Nation, One Election' policy.
title: Election results: BJP's core agenda gets a boost with heavy-Mahayuti win

description: Netflix is investigating a leak of unreleased footage from popular shows like Squid Game, believed to have originated from a security breach at post-production studio Lyuno. The streaming giant is working with Discord to identify the leaker, who allegedly shared copyrighted material, including an unreleased photo from Squid Game season two, on the platform.
title: 'Worst leak in streaming history': Our team is ..., update on ‘Netflix hack’
Maha polls: First in 6 decades, no LoP, as main oppn party wins under 10% of seats
US indictment: SEC issues summons to Adani, nephew Sagar

description: The IPL mega auction in Jeddah, Saudi Arabia is set to witness a fierce bidding war for top Indian cricketers. Rishabh Pant, Arshdeep Singh, and Shreyas Iyer are expected to command record-breaking bids. Pant's leadership and batting prowess, Arshdeep's exceptional death bowling, and Iyer's consistent performances have made them hot commodities.
title: IPL Auction: Pant, Rahul, Arshdeep, Iyer set to get mega deals

description: Diljit Dosanjh praised the Uttar Pradesh Police for their exceptional management of his recent concert at Lucknow's Ekana Stadium.  The singer expressed his gratitude on social media, calling it the best arrangement he had ever experienced. The UP Police responded with a playful tweet referencing Dosanjh's songs, which went viral, garnering thousands of likes and retweets.
title: Dil-jit liya: UP cops thank Diljit Dosanjh after singer’s praise

description: The Tamil Film Active Producers Association (TFAPA) is taking a stand against YouTubers, seeking to ban them from theaters and regulate online reviews. They allege YouTubers are engaging in malicious and personal attacks, impacting box office performance. TFAPA calls for industry unity to counter these practices, citing financial losses producers have suffered due to negative reviews.
title: 'Ban YouTubers entry in cinema halls', says furious Tamil film producers

description: A woman in Bhopal was detained by police for impersonating an Additional Superintendent of Police (ASP). She had been wearing the uniform to cheer up her ailing mother by pretending to have a job in the police force.
title: Bhopal: Jobless, woman dons fake cop uniform to please mom, detained

description: The Jharkhand Mukti Morcha (JMM)-led INDIA bloc secured a resounding victory in the Jharkhand assembly elections, winning 56 out of 81 seats.  JMM's success, attributed to its pro-tribal identity and welfare schemes, marks its first absolute majority since the state's formation in 2000. The BJP, despite its focus on infiltration issues, could only secure 24 seats.
title: SoReign in Jharkhand: JMM chief halts BJP story as state shows no 'infiltrators' fear

description: India's first Constitution Museum, inaugurated at OP Jindal Global University in Sonipat, showcases a rare copy of the Constitution and highlights the journey of its creation. The museum features interactive exhibits, including a hologram of Dr. B.R. Ambedkar and installations celebrating constitutional principles, offering visitors an immersive experience of India's constitutional history.
title: What’s in Constitution? India’s first such museum will tell you
BJP’s infiltration failed: Jharkhand shows no fear of ‘infiltrators’
Of 363 women in fray, only 22 make it to new Maharashtra assembly
Maha polls: Baramati embraces change, welcomes Dadagiri

description: The ruling Mahayuti alliance secured a landslide victory in the Maharashtra assembly elections, winning 230 out of 288 seats.  Key factors contributing to their win include the popularity of the Ladki Bahin Yojana cash transfer scheme for women, consolidation of OBC and pro-Hindutva votes, and strategic counter-campaigns addressing concerns raised during the previous Lok Sabha elections.
title: Maha polls: BJP's best, Cong's worst-ever show in state; 'Traitors' Shinde and Pawar true heirs

description: A video showing a government hospital nurse placing footwear near Mayiladuthurai Congress MLA S Rajakumar's feet during his hospital inspection sparked outrage and accusations of disrespect towards healthcare workers.  Rajakumar denied the allegations, stating he never forced the nurse and was about to wear footwear meant for the operation theatre when the nurse voluntarily assisted him.
title: Watch: Outrage over video of nurse carrying Congress MLA’s footwear in Tamil Nadu

description: Priyanka Gandhi has secured a massive victory in the Wayanad Lok Sabha byelection, further solidifying the Gandhi family's stronghold in the constituency. The LDF suffered a significant setback with its vote share plummeting to a historic low, while the NDA's candidate failed to make a substantial impact.
title: Wayanad reaffirms its status as all-weather pocket borough of Gandhi family

description: Uddhav Thackeray, Shiv Sena (UBT) chief, expressed shock at the unexpected assembly election results in Maharashtra. He questioned the reasons behind the outcome, citing concerns over economic issues and women's safety raised during the campaign. Thackeray vowed to continue fighting for the people of Maharashtra and expressed concerns over the future of opposition parties in the state.
title: Can’t believe Maharashtra would behave with me in this manner: Uddhav Thackeray

description: A 28-year-old Delhi Police constable, Kiranpal Singh, was fatally stabbed by three men in Govindpuri while on patrol duty.  Singh questioned the intoxicated men and attempted to check their belongings, leading to a scuffle. Two suspects, Deepak and Krish, are in custody, with Deepak sustaining a gunshot wound during arrest. The third suspect, Rocky, remains at large.
title: Young Delhi cop stops 3 drunk men for check, gets killed
Delhi air pollution: AQI turns ‘severe’ briefly, ‘very poor’ is current best

description: Hyderabad traffic police during a special drive found many two-wheeler riders without helmets citing excuses ranging from ruining hairstyles to causing dandruff. While some complained about helmets being suffocating, others admitted to carrying them without wearing them.  Authorities emphasize that helmets significantly reduce head injuries and fatalities during accidents, urging riders to wear them consistently for safety.
title: Spoiling hairstyle to religious beliefs: The many excuses of helmetless riders

Our astrologer has analyzed the movements of the planets and the alignment of the stars to bring you the most accurate and up-to-date horoscope predictions for the day ahead. Get ready to discover what the stars have in store for you today.
title: Horoscope Today, November 24, 2024: Read your astrological predictions
